Objectives / Learning Outcome(s) / Major:
1) COMMUNICATE THE NATURE OF COST ACCOUNTING AND ITS ROLE IN THE ORGANIZATION; 
2) ORGANIZE AND PRESENT INFORMATION IN A MANNER THAT IS USEFUL IN THE DECISION-MAKING PROCESS; 
3) CONSTRUCT ACCOUNTING REPORTS THAT CAN BE USED BY MANAGEMENT FOR DECISION-MAKING EVALUATION PURPOSES USING COMPUTER SOFTWARE OFTEN USED IN THE INDUSTRY; 
4) APPLY JOB ORDER AND ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING METHODS; 
5) APPLY BUDGETING, VARIANCE ANALYSIS, AND STANDARD COST CONCEPTS; AND
6) IDENTIFY RELEVANT COSTS AND REVENUES IN OPERATING AND INVESTMENT DECISION-MAKING SCENARIOS.
